{
  "texts": [
    "Lu and Li (2020) proposed a model called graph-aware co-attention network (GCAN) for predicting fake news based on the source tweet and its propagation through users.",
    "GCAN consists of five components.",
    "The first component extracts user characteristics that quantify the extent of a user's engagement in online social networking.",
    "User features are derived from their profiles and interactions within the social network.",
    "The second component encodes the news story by generating word embeddings for the source tweet."
  ]
}